We've got that.

00:02:25.700 --> 00:02:26.780
Drill.

00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:28.840
Drill bit, a 1-1/4
inch drill bit.

00:02:28.840 --> 00:02:30.760
And optionally, spray paint,

00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:33.560
and that's if you want to change
the color of the whole base.

00:02:34.080 --> 00:02:35.420
You don't need to do that,

00:02:35.420 --> 00:02:37.360
but it can look
a little slicker if you do.

00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:38.600
We want to drill
through both acrylic sheets

00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:40.700
and the wooden base
at the same time.

00:02:40.700 --> 00:02:43.200
That way, all of the holes are
going to be perfectly lined up.

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:45.300
And since we're drilling
all the way through this,

00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:46.780
we don't want to drill
into the workbench,

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:48.500
like I may have done
at some point in the past.

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:50.900
So we've got just
some scrap wood underneath it.

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:55.660
Masking tape is of course
the strongest type

00:02:55.660 --> 00:02:57.100
of tape in the world.

00:02:57.100 --> 00:02:58.880
&gt;&gt; Oh, wait, no, sorry.
&gt;&gt; This is undisputed.

00:02:58.900 --> 00:02:59.400
Sorry.

