00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:01.660
That's what I meant.

00:03:01.660 --> 00:03:02.400
But it should do
a pretty good job

00:03:02.406 --> 00:03:03.700
of holding everything in place.

00:03:03.700 --> 00:03:05.728
All we needed to do is
keep everything aligned

00:03:05.728 --> 00:03:07.360
as we drill holes into it.

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:08.592
Okay, we've got
the quarter inch drill bit,

00:03:08.592 --> 00:03:09.600
and we need to drill one,

00:03:09.600 --> 00:03:11.715
two, three holes
through all the acrylic

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:13.380
and the wooden base.

00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:15.050
And the one thing we
really need to make sure is

00:03:15.050 --> 00:03:16.300
that we have enough space

00:03:16.300 --> 00:03:19.240
in between these two
to fit our cell phone.

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:21.580
We want the camera
to be somewhere

00:03:21.580 --> 00:03:23.720
above this smaller rectangle.

00:03:23.720 --> 00:03:24.280
Okay.

00:03:24.280 --> 00:03:26.680
And we want to make sure we have
enough space on the sides

00:03:26.680 --> 00:03:28.500
that the phone fits nicely
in between the to.

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:29.760
When drilling acrylic,

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:32.520
you want to put
very little pressure,

00:03:32.560 --> 00:03:35.260
and just very carefully
drill down through it.

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:36.480
If you've got too much pressure,

00:03:36.480 --> 00:03:38.700
it's really likely to drill
through a lot of it,

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:39.980
and then at the back,

00:03:39.980 --> 00:03:41.460
when the acrylic sheet
gets really thin--

00:03:41.460 --> 00:03:42.360
It's gonna snap.

00:03:42.360 --> 00:03:43.740
It pushes through and snaps.

00:03:43.740 --> 00:03:44.860
So that's the second reason

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:46.500
that we've got things
stacked up like this.

00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:48.853
It does help with alignment,
but it also really helps

00:03:48.860 --> 00:03:50.720
with not pushing out the back.

00:03:50.720 --> 00:03:53.300
When the piece of acrylic
is pushed up against something else,

00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:55.200
the drill bit isn't going
to shove right through

00:03:55.200 --> 00:03:56.220
and break it.

00:03:56.220 --> 00:03:56.900
Hopefully, this will

00:03:56.900 --> 00:03:58.700
stop anything from
cracking and breaking.

00:03:58.700 --> 00:04:01.500
But just in case,
we do have another sheet.

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:03.100
Let's see how this goes.

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:05.760
Oh, we're into the wood.

